2500|$|The {{earliest}} {{books were}} handwritten by monks in scriptoria, with many flourishes and embellishments to letters. The controversy continues over readability, without conclusive results. Editors were formerly taught to use serif, as in older books. Magazines may use sans-serif as [...] "cleaner", but possibly decreasing readability. Modern e-book readers allow {{the viewer to}} adjust <b>font</b> <b>family</b> and size.|$|E
